# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# OpenFlows — Coder-Only Environment Configuration
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Copy to .env and fill in values. OpenFlows runs on top of a self-hosted
# Coder deployment. All LLM configuration happens in the Coder dashboard.

# ── Coder Server ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
CODER_URL=http://localhost:7080

# Admin credentials for initial bootstrap (first run only)
CODER_ADMIN_EMAIL=admin@openflows.dev
CODER_ADMIN_USERNAME=admin
CODER_ADMIN_PASSWORD=Op3nFl0ws!
CODER_PG_PASSWORD=coder
CODER_IMAGE_TAG=latest

# ── Redis SharedStore ────────────────────────────────────────────────────
REDIS_URL=redis://localhost:6379

# ── GitHub (required for issue/PR sync) ─────────────────────────────────────
# The Nexus agent uses this to fetch GitHub issues and track PRs.
#
# Option A — Coder External Auth (recommended, requires Coder premium):
#   Deployment → External Authentication → Add GitHub
#   Workspace automatically gets token via: coder external-auth access-token github
#
# Option B — Personal Access Token (fallback for dev setups):
#   https://github.com/settings/tokens → Generate new token (classic)
#   Required scope: repo
GITHUB_PERSONAL_ACCESS_TOKEN=ghp_your_token_here

# ── Notifications (optional) ─────────────────────────────────────────────
# SLACK_WEBHOOK_URL=https://hooks.slack.com/services/...
# DISCORD_WEBHOOK_URL=https://discord.com/api/webhooks/...